data.title: Meet The Team
data.meta_description: We are passionate about helping you achieve your business goals. Find out more about the AbeTech team here.
data.text:
Adam Hendrickson

I enjoy spending my free time with my family - whether its camping, boating, or just hanging out at home. When I am not spending time with family, I am typically in the garage working on one of many projects.

close

Adam Pietruszewski

I am an ardent lover of nature and spending time with my family. My favorite outdoor activities include camping, canoeing, disc golfing, snowboarding, and riding my hydrofoil. When forced inside, I enjoy brewing beer and playing the guitar. I have a very analytical mind and enjoy developing systems and solutions to address the problem at hand.

close

Alfredo Jimenez

I love spending time with my family, from going grocery shopping to hitting dirt bike trials with my son. There isn't much I do during the winter, but throughout the summer you'll definitely see me cruising around town in my old jeep with no top and no doors. Though there is nothing like cooling down at the river and having a picnic.

close

Allison Schmidt

Outside of work, I enjoy staying active, baking/cooking, reading, trying new restaurants/breweries with friends and family, and concert-going. I love yard games and spending time on the lake in the summer, and I love traveling as much as possible in the winter.

close

Amber Strenge

When away from the AbeTech team, I enjoy spending time with my family. A few hobbies of mine are camping, trail riding, and hanging out at my farm with my daughter. I also volunteer on search and rescue missions with my horses.

close

Andria Lenzen

I love spending my spare time with family and friends. Whether it is snowmobiling, ice fishing or enjoying a good book during the winter season. Once summer comes around you will find me on the lake soaking up the sun or ripping it up on my ATV. My husband and I have 2 teenage boys that keep us very busy, we love taking family vacations together. I also like to get out for a walk or run with our German Shepherd Cora.

close

Andy Doll

When not in the office or with clients, I enjoy spending time with my family at home. A hobby that my family and I enjoy doing together is hiking at the state parks in our area. Some personal hobbies of mine are playing Music (piano and guitar), woodworking, and DIY renovations.

close

Bailey Scotting-Veches

I love spending time with friends and family, preferably outdoors in the summertime. Whether that be camping, fishing, going to the cabin, and everything in between. We only have a few nice warm months in Minnesota, so I like to make the most of it. In the winter, you can find me traveling to warmer destinations, but truly just traveling in general. I love seeing new places and trying new things!

close

Becky Stumpf

Being a lifelong Minnesotan, I love to spend time at our cabin with family and friends. Summer on the lake just cant be beat. Unfortunately, we also have some very frigid weather in Minnesota. During that time, I dream and plan vacations to warm destinations. I also enjoy cooking and home improvement projects. Just ask my husband! I love sunshine, palm trees, and umbrella drinks. I hate snakes I mean, I despise snakes!!!

close

Ben Medina

My main hobbies are training for fitness competitions and trading equity derivatives. Outside of that, I'm passionate about spending time with my family and barbecuing on my offset smoker, reading, and watching movies with whatever free time I have!

close

Ben Zilmer

"Do you not know that those who run in a race all run, but only one receives the prize? Run in such a way that you may win." - 1 Corinthians 9:24

Read More

Ben Zilmer

I enjoy staying active and spending time with my family. I also enjoy working out, hunting, and playing basketball. In the summer, you can find me on a lake somewhere soaking in the sun.

close

Bill Schmidt

I spend as much time with my family as possible, hiking and biking in the summer/fall. In the winter, the family and I enjoy downhill skiing and snowshoeing at the cabin. I also like shooting and currently a bit of archery along with home improvement projects and yardwork/landscaping.

close

Bob Richards

I love spending time with my wife and 4 daughters. You will find me volunteering at church or working on DIY projects around the house in my spare time. Although I dont get to do this as much as I would like, camping or enjoying the Boundary Waters canoeing are among my favorite pastimes.

close

Brent Pollard

"Most People don't want to be part of the process but want to be a part of the outcome. What they don't understand is that the process is where we find out who's worthy of the outcome" - anonymous

Read More

Brooke Budhram

I love spending time at home with my cat and my family. In the evenings, you can find me playing video games, reading a book, or experimenting with new recipes. I also love to stay active by taking a spin class or doing Yoga.

close

Charlie Schmidt

I enjoy being on the go and keeping late hours. Charlie Jr. has moved from crawling to running everywhere he goes and wakes up at all hours of the night. I am no longer in control. Riding ATVs and snowmobiles are two of the things that take me out into the fresh air and on the hunt for the next adventure. I proudly hoist an American flag wherever I lay my head.

close

Chris Eliason

The vast majority of my time is spent supporting my kids lives these days by chauffeuring them between school, hockey rinks, and friends. During the summer weekends, I am often at the family cabin enjoying the water that is if Im not, again, at a hockey rink!

close

Christian Eberhart

I love spending time with my wife & 3 children, cooking outdoors, and all things music. In the summers, you will find me paddle boarding with the family on one of the many lakes & rivers in MN. I also love to play guitar, watch live music, or just about any sport or game.

close

Clay Hammock

At AbeTech, my off-hours are filled with the exhilaration of swimming and trail running, where I immerse myself in the tranquility of nature's landscapes. Alongside these adventures, I nurture a love for inventing, letting my imagination and problem-solving skills take the lead in crafting new gadgets, seamlessly blending physical vitality with creative innovation.

close

Darren Ludtke

Spring/Summer you can find me with my family at a campground. In the fall you can find me in a tree stand deer hunting. I'll be on the ice in Winter looking for a walleye.

close

David Davis

You, me, or nobody is gonna hit as hard as life. But it ain't about how hard you hit. It's about how hard you can get hit and keep moving forward; how much you can take and keep moving forward. That's how winning is done! - Anonymous

Read More

David Davis

I love quiet time and large cup of coffee while reading a book and relaxing with my family. During the fall and winter months I try my best to avoid the snow but love spending time in my hunting stand, rodeos, watching Ohio State Football, plotting on ways to get to a beach. During the spring and summer months Im at equestrian events, fishing, and trying to find the ocean. All other times I am probably at a theme park somewhere trying to find a new roller coaster. I believe between hard work and team efforts anything is possible.

close

David Rimmer

I enjoy traveling with my family, taking in Minnesota Wild games at other arenas around the league. During the summer, I enjoy exploring the great outdoors, disc golfing, and family bonfires. In the winter, you will find me sitting on the ice chasing after the elusive walleye.

close

Dean Chinni

I am fairly boring. I am an avid hockey fan, Love to go driving in the Texas Hill country with my wife. I play at guitar and bet on sports, but other than that have no real hobbies or outside interests. Work has been my hobby and still is, except when hockey is on. I am notorious for not being able to fix a thing around the house (or elsewhere), but I surprise on the upside every now and then.

close

Debbie Bicker

I enjoy spending time with family and friends. During the summer months, I enjoy swimming, floating, and camping. When I am not having fun, I am probably working on a landscape or gardening project. I also enjoy traveling and am happy sitting at home watching the sunset or roasting marshmallows around the fire pit.

close

Deborah Morey

Interacting with people and being immersed in the creative process are highlights for me. I enjoy going on adventures with my family, hosting parties, decorating and baking. I love to clothing shop with people who dont like to - to find the perfect outfit for that special occasion. My favorite place to be is by the ocean, near palm trees.

close

Eric Peter

I enjoy biking, rock climbing, backpacking, and being outside. I am an avid cyclist and own more than ten bikes for many uses, including extras for friends to borrow. I am a do-it-yourselfer and like designing, building, and painting home projects.

close

Eric Soderholm

My wife and I have two boys, so when I am not working or chasing the kids around to their activities, I can be found at the cabin, golf course, or on the ice in a fish house. Winters in Minnesota get long, so the family and I enjoy being able to escape to warmer climates each year and break out the shorts.

close

Erik Frost

I enjoy being with my wife and 2 kids. Sports that I enjoy are Nascar and Hockey. In my spare time I play drums in a country, red dirt band. Cibolo Rush if you want to look us up on Facebook. I am very hands on and like DIY projects, working on my wife's truck and just being outdoors. What is left of my free time is taken up with my daughter and her horse riding. It takes us all over the state and it is something that we love to watch her do and excel in.

close

Gao Ly Yang

I love to travel, hike, cook, and eat. During spring and summer time, I try to visit different state parks or go out of state with friends and/or family. When I want to relax, I usually choose to watch Netflix and eat popcorn with my family.

close

Garret Karels

I love spending time with my family and enjoy cooking. On weekends during warmer months, you will find me smoking foods and playing with new recipes. In the winter months, you will find me watching my kids play hockey or experimenting with new Sous-Vide recipes.

close

Gina Baumann

"Once you have traveled, the voyage never ends, but is played out over and over again in the quietest chambers, that the mind can never break off from the journey." Pat Conroy - The Prince of Tides

Read More

Holly Boutin

Outside of work I am generally happiest with a full social calendar and plenty of time with my family and friends. Minnesota summers are the best and live out of my camper most weekends. I love a good road trip as much as I love an airline ticket to warmth in the winter. I am a proud mom of one who is involved in dance and theater with no signs of slowing down.

close

Hunter Kivley

I enjoy the outdoors as well as watching sports with friends and family. I am one of those diehard Minnesota sports fan who unfortunately has never witnessed a championship in my lifetime. In the winter I tend to ice fish, while in the summer months I am either on the lake or you will find me on the course trying to improve my very average golf game. I like to think of myself as a hard-working and dedicated individual.

close

Jackie Carlson

I love spending time with family and friends. In the summer you can find me relaxing by a pool or going for a walk. In the winter, I enjoy traveling, skiing, and ice fishing. I am a great multi-tasker and like being very organized.

close

Jake Moser

I love anything outdoors, long excursions in the Boundary Waters, rock climbing in the Tetons, Skiing in the Rockies, playing cribbage while lakeside, I'll take what I can get. I also enjoy getting hands-on with projects, whether it's automotive work or remodeling my house. I'm a big proponent of type 2 fun.

close

Jason Bridwell

A lifetime resident of beautiful Montana, I take full advantage of the outdoors by hiking, mountain biking, hunting and fishing with my family and close friends. My faith and my family are my priority with four grown children and now 5 grandchildren that my wife and I adore spending quality time with. I have a background in carpentry and enjoy projecting and helping friends and family with home repairs and renovations. Professionally I am passionate about investing in the development of lasting relationships with co-workers, business partners, and clients . . . always with the goal of helping others succeed.

close

Jason Velcheck

I have seen the USA in a Chevrolet. Five consecutive summer road trips; all 48 states. When I am not planning our next road adventure, I can be found cursing at a woodworking project gone wrong, watching my son coach youth hockey, working on barbeque that is always short of "just right" or playing an ongoing game of cribbage, five crowns, or triominos with my wife. I have two dogs that have never met a treat that wasn't the world's best.

close

Jennifer Toepper

When not at work, you can find me chauffeuring my kids to dance, football and hockey. With my (little) downtime between practices, games, and dance competitions, you will find me relaxing on a patio or around a bonfire with friends.

close

Jeremy Hogan

I played Golf. I did not get a hole in one. But I did hit a guy. Thats way more satisfying. Youre supposed to yell FORE. I was too busy yelling There aint no way thats going to hit him!!

Read More

Joan Bean

When not in the office, I enjoy spending time with family and friends. In the summer, you can find me boating and enjoying the outdoors. In the winter, I enjoy working on DIY projects around the house.

close

Jonathan Reid

I enjoy learning and teaching new graphic design software programs and creating videos for non-profits and educational institutions. In my free time, you can find me spending time outside on the disc golf course, even in the snow! Close to my heart are my Special Olympics softball and bowling teams, which I coach in the winter and spring.

close

Jose Jimenez

I love spending time with the family, especially our Friday movie night. I like to cool down at the river during summer and work on cars and keep my yard in good shape.

close

Jose Rodriguez

I love the outdoors and everything about it, especially water and snow activities. I have always had a can-do mentality and I am grateful to have a great family that is also very hardworking.

close

Julie Osmundson

I love spending time with family and friends. In the summer, I enjoy walking my dogs, gardening, fishing, boating, and spending weekends up north at my camper. In the winter, I enjoy ice fishing and traveling.

close

Julie Pepper

I love spending time with my family. Most of my free time is spent up north at the family cabin. I like the outdoors, taking walks in the woods, fishing, and relaxing by the fire. On cold winter days, I spend my time reading books. I enjoy my roll at AbeTech and am proud to be a part of the AbeTech Family!

close

Keaton Bock

"Remember, that when you got there, you didn't get there alone. When you got there, there were people who took that time out of their lives to help you get there. And you owe something to the people after you who still want to get there too." - Marc Bernardin

Read More

Keaton Bock

When out of the office, I enjoy spending time with my family and my dog. I like to fill my time watching movies, listening to music, podcasts, playing video games, and the occasional project around the house or in the garage.

close

Kevin Moshier

With my time away from work, I enjoy traveling, playing video/board games, and most of all cooking. I am a connoisseur in food and beverages and am always trying new recipes and sometimes creating my own.

close

Kris Boles

When not at work, I enjoy spending time with my family and friends. I love working in my garden, reading, and playing tennis. I consider myself a half-glass full kind of girl, as I have been a Cleveland Browns Fan since birth, forever hopeful that this will be their year! A perfect day for me is a warm, sunny day at the beach, enjoying the sounds of laughter from family and the roar of the ocean.

close

Krista Dahlheimer

I love spending time with my family and friends! If I am not at one of my kid's sporting events, you can usually find me at a social gathering or enjoying a bonfire in the backyard with friends! I really love all animals and if it were up to me, I would have a zoo in my backyard. I am a positive person and I make sure to surround myself with good vibes and fun people.

close

Kyle Braasch

I enjoy a constant challenge in my free time. In the warmer months I can be found operating heavy machinery at the farm or out in the garage working with power tools. In the colder months I like to work on my home lab and take my snowboard out.

close

Lyndsey Novak

When I am not in the office working, I enjoy spending time outdoors in every season. A few hobbies of mine are overland style camping with my family, spending time on the boat, hitting the ATV trails, bringing the dogs to the dog park, and ice fishing. I also enjoy keeping busy with crafts and projects around her home.

close

Marc Lawson

The Great Secret of Life is the law of attraction. The law of attraction can also be called the law of creation. In other words, life is not happing to you, you are creating it!  Author unknown

Read More

Mark Harris

When I am not working, you can find me at the softball fields watching my daughter play fastpitch during the spring and summer. I am an avid BBQ aficionado and enjoy putting my own twist on new BBQ recipes. In the rare instances we aren't at a ballfield, I can be found on the lake fishing and enjoying what Minnesota has to offer! I am a student of history, and any chance I get to learn more, I take it.

close

Mary Bergeron

I am a child sports enthusiast. If there is soccer, wrestling, gymnastics, diving, Lacrosse, track, or any other sport my kids want to add to the list- I can be found on the sidelines twelve months per year! When I am not at sporting events, I enjoy gardening, doing barre classes, and going for walks.

close

Matt Ladwig

When I am not behind my monitors working, I am spending time with my family. One hobby that my family and I enjoy doing together is going to the lake.

close

Matt Schwarz

I'm a sports nut who loves live music and spending time with my family. A life-long soccer player who jumps at the chance to kick a ball around whenever I can. My favorite time of the year is fall because that means college football. Hook 'em! I'm obsessed with music and I'm pretty much always up for a live show no matter who's playing.

close

Michael Mundale

When away from the office you will find me with my family supporting our daughters in their activities. As a family we love camping, swimming, hiking, bike riding, and being in the great outdoors. When I have time to myself you will find me in my woodworking shop. I love to hunt, fish, and cook meat on the smoker.

close

Michelle Kelly

My passions are cooking and gardening. Im always cooking something and in winter, Ill do some crafting projects indoors. When its not winter, you will find me outside working in my small perennial flower garden and growing vegetables in pots. Whenever possible, I love to spend time with my very large family in Indiana.

close

Mitchell Heusmann

More than anything, I enjoy spending time with family & friends. Add in some good food, drinks & music and it's hard to beat that. I love the outdoors, traveling to new places and meeting new people. I'm a huge college football & basketball fan and if the Bengals happen to string a few wins together I love the NFL. In the summers, my ideal day starts with a good run or bike ride, followed by a round of golf or trip the lake and ends with firing up the grill/bonfire.

close

Nathan Khan

I enjoy the seasonal activities that Minnesota has to offer. Celebrating the end of winter in the spring, outdoor activities in the summer and fall, then hiding indoors in the winter. I love talking about golf, cars, technology, and gaming. I am also a bit of a foodie and love cooking and trying new restaurants. When not at work I spend my time with my wife Kate and dog Bravo.

close

Nicole Johns-Votel

I love baseball season it's the one sport I look forward to every year, while watching my son play. I also spending time with family outside while creating new memories.

close

Oscar Sanchez

When not working, I enjoy spending time outdoors. One hobby of mine that I am super passionate about is riding my motorcycle. My wife and I love going on cross country motorcycle trips together. When we are not on the motorcycle, we are in our teardrop camper, camping out! We enjoy traveling to visit family that lives in West TX and KS. A few other hobbies of mine are automotive/mechanic work and woodworking. My wife and I also enjoy tackling projects around our new home, lately that has been landscaping.

close

Parker Butler

I love my job for the same reasons I love hunting and fishing. Changing environments and conditions, targeting something with a mind of its own, read-interpret-react-execute-repeat. They are all very humbling hobbies but can be extremely rewarding when the plan comes together. They all challenge me to be creative and learn new tactics.

close

Patsy Hanson

I enjoy being outdoors during the warmer weather months, walking with friends, and planting/caring for my flowers. In the winter, I enjoy watching movies and doing home improvement projects with my husband.

close

Paul Rehovsky

I enjoy skiing, snowshoeing, fishing, and mountain biking with my family. You might also see me navigating rocky trails in my old Land Cruiser, smoking meat in the back yard, or gardening. I also like to geek out on computers and home automation.

close

Peter Schnellman

A Nation can survive its fools, and even the ambitious. But it cannot survive treason from within. An enemy at the gates is less formidable, for he is known and carries his banner openly. But the traitor moves amongst those within the gate freely, his sly whispers rustling through all the alleys, heard in the very halls of government itself. - Marcus Tullius Cicero

Read More

Peter Schnellman

I am the proud father of two delightful daughters. I very much enjoy working with my hands - particularly woodworking. If I am not in the shop cutting and gluing pieces of wood together, I am in our yard grooming, thinning, and curating our woods. I am never idle and always have some project or concept for a project brewing. I am a warm weather person, and any temperature less than 85 degrees is COLD.

close

Rick Segal

I love spending time with my kids any chance I can get. When the lakes are not frozen, I will be out fishing and enjoying being outside as often as I can. I am not a fan of the winter, so living in Minnesota, I have to get creative and work on projects inside. I stay active by running and working on outside projects.

close

Riley Crabtree

My family is my world and we are always getting into something...as long as it's warm out! On the weekends during the summer you can find me road tripping to a dirt track to cheer on my better half. When it comes winter time, I'll be under a blanket next to a fire dreaming about sunshine and sunburns. I am a sucker for over priced coffee, sweet wine and any home renovation TV show.

close

Roger Flores

I am a dynamic music lover. From Tejano to Death Metal, I love it all! I have been playing drums for over 20 years. An avid gamer on the weekends, catch me online!

close

Ross Anderson

I like to consider myself a bit of an indoors man. However, when the temperature dips beneath 70 degrees, you can find me battling metro golf courses or trying to avoid injury on the softball diamond. I also enjoy getting emotionally invested in the local professional sports teams each season just to have my heart broken each year.

close

Ryan Burgett

I love sports and the outdoors. You can find me at a Cubs baseball game or working on my golf game during the spring. A few hobbies of mine are woodworking and DIY projects around the house. I am not afraid to dive headfirst into any project, and my passion shows through in all that I do.

close

Stephanie Dietrich

Most of my time is spent driving my kids to their activities. Hockey and dance! When I'm not driving I'm in the stands cheering them on :) I love spending my time with family, friends, and my standard Goldendoodle, Remi. :)

close

Stephanie O'Keefe

When I am not at Abetech, I spend my time running kids around to all their sports and spending time with my family. We LOVE anything outdoors, camping, kayaking, hiking and checking state parks off of our list! We recently renovated a small vintage camper and has become quite the passion of ours. Would love to someday travel the US camping.

close

Steve Schmidt

For over 30 years, I have been fortunate to work with a wide variety of amazing folks that have helped to shape the success of the company. When listening closely and delivering on promises to clients, good things seem to happen for everyone.

When my wife allows for it, endurance sports such as ultra-running, mountain-climbing and mountain biking are my current passions.

close

Tammy Carniel

"Sometimes the bad things that happen in our lives puts us directly on the path to the best things that will ever happen to us." - Anonymous

Tammy Carniel

I love the outdoors when it's summer, but I struggle quite a bit during winter time, as I dislike being cold. During winter I spend a lot of time indoors. Don't get me wrong, I do go out during winter, but to stay inside somewhere else.

Since I was little I liked nail designs, so when I am not working, I am probably doing someone else's nails. I even have an Instagram page where I post all my designs.

close

Tammy Sewray

I love spending time with my family and friends! In the summer I enjoy relaxing by the pool, four wheeling or out on the lake fishing. During the winter you will find me in the Ice Castle ice fishing and enjoying time with my family.

close

Taylor Bekken

I love the outdoors and spending time with family. In the winter, you can find me snowboarding or ice fishing. During the summer months, I will most likely be playing frisbee golf or floating on the water. I also have a do-it-yourself mentality. I enjoy tackling hands-on projects like automotive work, landscaping, and carpentry.

close

Taylor Frost

I am a hobby baker in my spare time, with a mild sprinkle addiction. When in doubt, always add more sprinkles! If Im not in the kitchen baking, you can find me in the barn with my pony, Auzzie. I am a chauffeur to 2 beautiful kids and I am lucky enough to get to work with my husband (go check out his picture!).

close

Tim Gribler

I spend my summers playing golf, tennis, and wake surfing. My family and I enjoy traveling across the country and around the world. Reading and hanging with friends is how I relax in my spare time.

close

Tim Holzmann

Tim Holzmann

When I am not working, I enjoy eating good food and watching shows about food and food culture, historical documentaries, and movies with more dialog than CGI. On a pleasant spring or fall day and all holidays, I will most likely be grilling or smoking something for a meal that day. I enjoy sports and when I get the chance will be on the golf course with two of my four daughters. Activities with my family are most important to me whether it be at home an event or our church.

close

Tim O'Leary

I am a Rock n Roll enthusiast and enjoy the live music scene, especially with family. I am an avid fan of THE Ohio State Buckeyes & Columbus Blue Jackets and like to take in the occasional Rugby Match. When I need to blow off steam, I can be found walking or riding my bike around the local parks or putting in work at the gym.

close

Tim Sullivan

I enjoy spending my time away from the office with my family. My hobbies include camping, cruising the lake on the pontoon, riding on my Harley, or golfing. I enjoy all sports, particularly college football, which you can find me watching most Saturdays - Minnesota Gophers or Notre Dame Fighting Irish.

close

Todd Jacobs

Passion for technology is in my blood. Ever since a ninth-grade computer science class where we made a stick man go across the screen programming in machine language and getting on the internet after my parents bought me a modem in 1986, I have been hooked. I very much enjoy serving and have been on five mission trips (Guatemala and Honduras) where I get a chance to practice speaking Spanish and live out my Christian faith. Outside of work, I like to be outside, play video games, RC cars/planes/drones, motorsports, fishing and obviously, embrace technology in most everything I do.

close

Tracey Jones

I am an avid outdoorsman and enjoy farming, camping. A few hobbies that I enjoy doing with the family are hunting and fishing. When I am not working or spending time with my family, I enjoy serving in the community as a high school wrestling coach. I am a Board Member of our Property Owners Association and a member of the Arkansas Realtors Association, where I am a Principal Broker.

close

Travis Rhodes

I love my faith, family and friends. I am lighthearted and love to laugh with friends. I was born and raised in the South but currently on the West Coast. Past time fun includes: kayaking/canoeing, hockey, football, baseball, dirt bikes, motorcycles, traveling, drones, video games, hiking and outdoor activities. Present time fun includes: hanging out with my wife, family and friends, taking our dog to eat at "lazy dog", sunny beaches & palm trees, exploring new places to eat; especially water front with live music.

close

Troy Norman

Obstacles dont have to stop you. If you run into a wall, dont turn around and give up. Figure out how to climb it, go through it, or work around it.  Michael Jordan

Troy Norman

I am a sports fan  you will often find me in the stands at local football, basketball, or baseball games. I enjoy golfing, fishing (summer and winter), snowmobiling, and hanging with friends and family. A more recent hobby would be my interest in craft beer and visiting many craft breweries throughout Minnesota.

close

Vasili Semos

My family moved from Greece when I was two years old. I am the luckiest man in the world to have a loving wife and daughter that tolerate my shenanigans. I enjoy spending time with lifelong friends and family having dinner, or just visiting. Love chasing a little white ball around a golf course and am approaching 20 years of playing Fantasy Football (only one championship). I went to the University of Memphis when it was known as Memphis State (Go Tigers Go). What I love about my job is the interaction and connection with people. I have friends that happen to be clients.

close

Wendy Martin

I love spending my free time hanging out with the family. I have recently become an empty nester, which I am not happy about. I have two small dogs that I enjoy snuggling with and taking for walks. When not at work, I enjoy spending time at our cabin in northern Minnesota, spending time with family and friends, reading, target shooting, and taking walks.

close

Will McGraw

I love watching sports, staying active and hanging out with friends and family. In spring/summer I like going out for runs in local parks and playing a little golf. In fall/winter I like watching college football and hockey and hitting the hard water for some ice fishing.

close

Wilson Yang

"You put water into a cup, it becomes the cup. You put water into a bottle, it becomes the bottle. You put it into a teapot, it becomes the teapot. Now water can flow or it can crash. Be water, my friend." - Bruce Lee

Wilson Yang

On my Free time Im a Gamer and an outdoor person, Im very family oriented and I love to play sports and be active, but FOOD is more important! Overall I just want to enjoy life and make the best of it! Im a all-season person, as long as its fun and seems like a good outcome, Im up for it! Its not about how good youre at it but its about the effort you put to it! Remember A for (A)Effort!

close

Xong Lor

I enjoy hiking with my dog, learning new skills and watching horror films. I'm passionate about drawing and writing short stories as a hobby as well. When I'm not at work, I spend most of my time with my family.
